    {
      "id": "alphabet",
      "icon": "🔤",
      "title": "Alphabet",
      "subtitle": "L-alfabett Malti — 30 letters",
      "facts": [
        "The Maltese alphabet has 30 letters: 24 consonants and 6 vowels (a, e, i, o, u, ie).",
        "Although ie is two symbols, it counts as one vowel.",
        "Five letters are unique to Maltese: ċ, ġ, ħ, ż, and għ (għ counts as one consonant).",
        "Each letter has a specific sound — Maltese is mostly phonetic, so most words are pronounced as they're written.",
        "Maltese has a Semitic base from Arabic, with strong influence from Italian and English."
      ],
